Grandpa, I don’t have the words to express how much you have meant to myself and to our entire family.  Your love, support, witty humor and smarts were all unmatched.  I’ll truly miss chatting business and Chicago Bears with you and I can’t thank God enough for having you in my life.  I am so grateful to have spent time with you a few weeks back in Atlanta and that I got to see you again for Christmas ❤️ I love you Grandpa, thank you for all of the memories

Story Time.  This photo is from the premiere for my skate video ‘STRIVE’ back in early 2008.  My Grandpa gave me a loan to rent out a local theatre for two showings, this would be our first ‘business transaction’. Despite the premiere falling on what became the worst blizzard the area had seen in years, the showings filled up.  I was able pay my Grandpa back promptly with ticket and DVD sales from the night.  He had unwavering belief in me. ‘STRIVE’ went on to gain a small local cult following across the midwest and this night would become instrumental to my future.  Shortly after this, I used the profits to pursue my dreams and head west to California.  I couldn’t have done it without my Grandpa and can’t thank him enough ❤️

Unfortunately, I did not plan to be writing this whilst curled up in a ball of sickness on my couch, yet here we are.  In fact, my plan for today was to go into The Berrics and lay on the ground, look up to the BATB banners and soak up 15 years of memories.  Perhaps I will do that tomorrow.  Anywho, today I celebrate my 15 year anniversary of working at @berrics  Nearly half of my life.  Along this journey, there have been many highs and many lows, and I assure you there has been both…but I wouldn’t trade any of it.  If you would have told me 15 years ago that I would be in this position, I’m not sure I would have believed you…it’s been beyond a dream come true.  Not only that, up until this point, I think my longest employment was 6 months working at Target.  Thank you to @steveberra and @erickoston for believing in me and thank you to every professional skater, brand and coworkers past and present for giving me the chance to help us grow together. 🤝🫡

Finally getting around to my 2023 recap; a year that has been the most eventful, special, important, pivotal and amazing year of my life ❤️🙏 Narrowing this down to 10 photos was no simple task and could never paint the full picture.  Although, the year did start off rough, with the passing of my Grandpa who has been my idol for my entire life.  I learned to accept that it was his time and I am so thankful to have had him in my life.  Once again, I had the opportunity to travel the world for both business and pleasure.  Lore even took me on a cruise (my first ever) to Mexico!  In March, I celebrated my 15 year anniversary at the @berrics  and not too long after, in mid June, I decided it was time for me to take the next steps in my life and move on from The Berrics.  Shortly after that, my brother and I decided to start our own business as we launched @storiedskateboarding & @thestrivecollaborative with the @tonyhawk “The Perfect Storm” piece.  We were (and still are) overwhelmed with the response it receieved.  Even @liltunechi gave us a shoutout!  I had a silly idea to ask some people if they ‘used to skate’ with my friends @toreypudwill & @prod and that also garnered an unbelievably positive response.  @chrisjoslin_ and I worked on a whole heap of rad projects together. I will be forever grateful for his trust and his help, as these projects were huge for the growth of STORIED.  My girlfriend and I celebrated Bear dog’s 11th Birthday with a little beach party!  My brother @claytongabor got married to @la_tigresa and we celebrated in New Mexico the best way possible, with family and a squad of childhood friends.  I enjoyed another great year of @sls not only during the events themselves, but hanging out with the crew before and after 🍻 Most importantly, in August, my girlfriend @lore.be and I found out we are pregnant with Baby Leo who is due in just a few months 👶🏼🥳 Thank you to everybody for the support, thanks to all my friends and family and I am looking forward to an even more amazing and important year going into 2024. Time to be a Dad!
